  "texts": [
    "In addition to collaborative discussions, several works explore socially-aligned and self-collaborative paradigms.",
    "For instance, Liu et al. [79] construct sandbox environments to curate behavior-aligned datasets and train LLMs with enhanced social alignment.",
    "Wang et al. [80] propose a self-collaboration method, where a single LLM is prompted with multi-persona roles, simulating multiagent communication internally.",
    "This reduces communication latency while preserving the benefits of role diversity.",
    "• Multi-robot & Embodied Agents."
  ],
